The paper deals with the theory of quantum computation and computability, which is closely related to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of quantum mechanics in computing, which falls under the subfield of quantum computing (cs.QL). The paper also involves mathematical logic and set theory, which are topics in the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant to the paper as it deals with the quantification, storage, and communication of information. Finally, the paper discusses the concept of functions, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
